goto https://ckeditor.com/ckeditor-5/online-builder/
choose Classic Editor
select plugins (see plugins.txt)
configure toolbar
build and download
unzip and rename to ckeditor5
copy folder to resources folder
Add required plugins to package.json (or do that later)
navigate terminal to ckeditor5 folder
execute npm install
modify /src/ckeditor.js to suit your requirements (adding plugins, toolbar sequence)
execute yarn run build (or npm run build)
/build/ckeditor.js is now updated
if the publishing of ckeditor is handled in webpack.mix.js => navigate to root and execute npm run dev

Example adding plugin (autosave)
npm install --save @ckeditor/ckeditor5-autosave
add import AutoSave from '@ckeditor/ckeditor5-autosave/src/autosave.js'; to src/editor.js
add AutoSave to Editor.builtinPlugins array.
yarn run build